Market Analysis and Size

Kiteboarding is a popular recreational activity in countries with large bodies of water. Kiteboarding has experienced an increase in popularity over the last few years all around the world. Many individuals are participating in activities such as outdoor and adventure sports, such as kiteboarding. The kiteboarding equipment business is fuelled by people's growing disposable money and their desire for adventure. People are becoming more inclined to spend money on leisure activities. Models, actors, and athletes enjoy kiteboarding because it allows them to stay in shape.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global kiteboarding equipment market which was USD 378.40 million in 2022, is expected to reach USD 885.51 million by 2030, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 10.2% during the forecast period of 2023 to 2030. “Kiteboards” dominates the type segment of the global kiteboarding equipment market as they are fundamental to the sport, and every kiteboarder, whether a beginner or advanced rider, requires one. This inherent necessity ensures a consistent demand for kiteboards. In addition to the market insights such as market value, growth rate, market segments, geographical coverage, market players, and market scenario, the market report curated by the Data Bridge Market Research team includes in-depth expert analysis, import/export analysis, pricing analysis, production consumption analysis, and consumer behaviour.

